Construct a custom-fit flying machine with woodcarver's tools over a long rest. It can be used as a spellcasting focus by you and can be worn over light armor; you can only have one at a time. Gain the following benefits from it:
When you fall while not incapactitated, subtract 100 ft. from fall damage calculation, and you can move 2 ft. horiontally for every ft. descended;
You gain a 60-ft. flying speed;
When you make a weapon attack while at least 5 ft. off the ground, use Intelligence for the attack and damage rolls;
You can Dash as a bonus action;;
You gain +{{intelligence:modifier}} to Dexterity ability checks and saving throws; if a Dexterity saving throw specifies that you take half damage if you succeed, instead take no damage on a success and half damage on a failure

When you merge wtih your Chimera:
RYou can use Intelligence whenever Strength is called for in attack and damage rolls, ability checks, or saving throws;
You gain a climbing speed equal to your movement speed and can climb difficult terrain without an ability check;
RYou can use a bonus action to expend a spell slot and grant yourself temporary hit points equal to five times the spell slot level + {{modifier:intelligence}}; these are added to the temporary hit points you gain from merging with your Chimera.

Construct a set of Marionette Strings during a long rest. You can cause them to fly out up to 30 ft. and attach to a willing creature as an action. As long as you have a free hand you gain use of the following:
Corrected Strike: When the attached creature makes a melee attack, use a reaction before the result is known to have them reroll the attack roll, and they must use the new roll;
Channel Spell: As an action you can cast an artificer spell originating from the attached creature (you still concentrate on spells that require it);
Puppeteer's Guidance: When the attached creature makes an ability check using a skill you are proficient in, grant them +{{intelligence:modifier}} on the roll;
Strange Movement: As a bonus action on your turn you can move the attached creature {{strange movement feet}} ft. wtihout it provoking opportunity attacks

Construct a set of Marionette Strings during a long rest. You can cause a set to fly out up to 60 ft. and attach to a willing creature as an action. As long as you have a free hand you gain use of the following abilities; you can control two sets of Strings at once as long as you have two free hands:
Corrected Strike: When the attached creature makes a melee attack, use a reaction before the result is known to have them reroll the attack roll, and they must use the new roll;
Strange Strikes: When the attached creature makes an attack, use a reaction for them to make an additional attack;
When the attached creature hits with a melee attack, expend a spell slot to deal an additional 2d6 force damage + 1d6 per level over the 1st;
Channel Spell: As an action you can cast an artificer spell originating from the attached creature (you still concentrate on spells that require it);
Puppeteer's Guidance: When the attached creature makes an ability check using a skill you are proficient in, grant them +{{intelligence:modifier}} on the roll;
Strange Movement: As a bonus action on your turn you can move the attached creature {{strange movement feet}} ft. wtihout it provoking opportunity attacks

Construct a set of Marionette Strings during a long rest; you can have two at a time. You can cause them to fly out up to 30 ft. and attach to a willing creature as an action. As long as you have a free hand you gain use of the following:
Corrected Strike: When the attached creature makes a melee attack, use a reaction before the result is known to have them reroll the attack roll, and they must use the new roll;
Strange Strikes: When the attached creature makes an attack, use a reaction for them to make an additional attack;
When the attached creature hits with a melee attack, expend a spell slot to deal an additional 2d6 force damage + 1d6 per level over the 1st;
Channel Spell: As an action you can cast an artificer spell originating from the attached creature (you still concentrate on spells that require it);
Puppeteer's Guidance: When the attached creature makes an ability check using a skill you are proficient in, grant them +{{intelligence:modifier}} on the roll;
Strange Movement: As a bonus action on your turn you can move the attached creature {{strange movement feet}} ft. wtihout it provoking opportunity attacks
